Hi, and welcome back to Line Sheet. It=E2=80=99s Frieze Week in Los Angeles=
, and
while pretty much every luxury brand ducked out of this year=E2=80=99s fair=
 due to the fires, a lot is still happening. Last night, I drove 10 minutes=
 down Eagle Rock Boulevard to Glassell Park for a studio party in the build=
ing occupied by Hilary Pecis, Lily Stockman, Jake Longstreth, and other gre=
at Eastside artists=E2=80=A6 and saw far more friends than anticipated. Los=
 Angeles is small in that way. While you don=E2=80=99t run into people on t=
he street as in New
York, you do tend to see the same 25-30 people at social events. (Like Jaso=
n Stewart. I can=E2=80=99t seem to shake him.)=C2=A0

=C2=A0

The actual fair, all the way out at the Santa Monica Airport, starts Thursd=
ay=E2=80=94a pre-Oscar-weekend novelty of sorts. It got me thinking about t=
his time last year, when Staud designer Sarah Staudinger hosted a fab Friez=
e Los Angeles kickoff dinner with her
friend Jeffrey Deitch. (Staudinger=E2=80=99s husband, of course, is Endeavo=
r co-founder and C.E.O. Ari Emanuel, who owns Frieze and is currently tryin=
